PART 2 — INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY DISPOSITION CLAUSE
================================================================================

The following terms govern the sale, transfer, or exclusive licensing of the
Software's intellectual property rights ("IP Disposition"):

A. MINIMUM VALUATION FLOOR

   The IP rights to this Software (including patents, trademarks, trade
   secrets, and copyrights held by the project) SHALL NOT be sold,
   exclusively licensed, or otherwise transferred to any third party for
   a total consideration below the following thresholds:

   - Year 1  (April 7, 2026 — April 6, 2027):   $100,000,000 USD
   - Year 2  (April 7, 2027 — April 6, 2028):    $1,000,000,000 USD
   - Year 3  (April 7, 2028 — April 6, 2029):    $10,000,000,000 USD
   - Year N  (each subsequent year):              10x the prior year's floor

   "Total consideration" includes cash, stock, earn-outs, royalties, and any
   other form of value received by the selling parties.

B. PROCEEDS DISTRIBUTION

   Any proceeds from an IP Disposition SHALL be distributed as follows:

   - 33%  — Nephilim Venture Capital (or its successors/assigns)
   - 33%  — Core Team (as defined in GOVERNANCE.md)
   - 33%  — Community Contributors (pro-rata by contribution weight as
             defined in GOVERNANCE.md)
   -  1%  — Security Bounty Reserve (held for ongoing security research
             and vulnerability disclosure rewards)

C. GOVERNANCE APPROVAL

   Any IP Disposition requires approval from:
   - Nephilim Venture Capital (or its designated representative), AND
   - A supermajority (2/3) of the Core Team as listed in GOVERNANCE.md

D. NON-EXCLUSIVE LICENSING

   Nothing in this clause restricts non-exclusive commercial licensing,
   SaaS offerings, support contracts, or other revenue activities that
   do not constitute a full transfer of IP rights. Such revenues are
   governed by the project's governance documents.

